cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CE, cs.SY 

The paper presents a new global optimization algorithm inspired by the influence of leaders in social groups. This algorithm is designed into a group architecture and is applied to various optimization problems, including quantum circuit design. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) due to the optimization focus of the paper. The paper also discusses the efficiency of the algorithm, which could place it in the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category. Finally, the application of the algorithm to quantum circuit design could place it in the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
